%e A057650 a(12)=1065 since with g(2) = 12 = 2^(2+1) + 2^2, we get g(3) = 3^(3+1) + 3^3 - 1 = 107 = 3^(3+1) + 2*3^2 + 2*3 + 2 and g(4) = 4^(4+1) + 2*4^2 + 2*4 + 2 - 1 = 1065.
%e A057650 a(17) = 4^(4^4) - 1, with g(2) = 17 = 2^(2^2) + 1 and g(3) = 3^(3^3).
%e A057650 Similarly a(18) = 4^(4^4) + 1, with g(2) = 18 = 2^(2^2) + 2 and g(3) = 3^(3^3) + 2.
